pullRequest.body:
We change the definition of a strong monoidal functor from a lax monoidal functor for which the unitor and tensorator are `IsIso` to a lax monoidal functor with the data of inverses for the unitor and tensorator. This requires fixing a lot of knock on effects.

---

This is a **draft PR**. I would like to talk with people on zulip before merging it, and plan ahead to when we have oplax/colax monoidal functors as well. I'm not sure the approach I took here where `MonoidalFunctor` inherits from `LaxMonoidalFunctor` is a good choice if we want to be lax/oplax symmetric.

nodes.body: Please do not break the `simp?` pattern, which facilitates the maintenance of the code.
Sorry, I'm not sure why I changed that. It's been changed back
Ah, now it's timing out and breaking the build. What would you suggest here?
Add `set_option maxHeartbeats 400000 in` before the declaration should make it work. (This increase is necessary only when it is compiled with `set_option says.verify true`, e.g. during CI)
Hm, okay. It would be nice for these proofs to not use nonterminal simps

I had left this nonterminal simp. It would be better to replace it with the following code and its output:
```lean
    simp [mappingConeHomOfDegreewiseSplitXIso, mappingCone.ext_from_iff _ _ _ rfl,
      mappingCone.inl_v_d_assoc _ (p + 1) _ (p + 1 + 1) (by linarith) (by linarith),
      cocycleOfDegreewiseSplit, r_f] says
I changed it like you suggested. I had to change it in the first place because the nonterminal simp was newly exceeding 200000 heartbeats
